# Task

Create metadata types that describe signature fields at compile time.

## File to Create/Modify
`crates/dspy-rs/src/core/signature.rs` (alongside or replacing MetaSignature)

## Types to Define

```rust
/// Describes a single field in a signature (input or output)
pub struct FieldSpec {
    /// LLM-facing name (may be aliased via #[alias("name")])
    pub name: &'static str,

    /// Rust struct field identifier
    pub rust_name: &'static str,

    /// Doc comment from field (used in prompts)
    pub description: &'static str,

    /// Function returning TypeIR for this field
    /// Why fn pointer: TypeIR isn't const-constructible
    pub type_ir: fn() -> TypeIR,

    /// Constraints defined on this field
    pub constraints: &'static [ConstraintSpec],
}

/// A constraint defined via #[check] or #[assert] attribute
pub struct ConstraintSpec {
    pub kind: ConstraintKind,

    /// User-provided label (required for check, optional for assert)
    pub label: &'static str,

    /// The constraint expression (e.g., "this >= 0.0 && this <= 1.0")
    pub expression: &'static str,
}

/// Distinguishes soft (check) from hard (assert) constraints
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]
pub enum ConstraintKind {
    /// Soft constraint - failure recorded in metadata but not an error
    Check,
    /// Hard constraint - failure causes ParseError::AssertFailed
    Assert,
}
```

## Why Static Lifetimes?

All data is compile-time constant:
- `name`, `rust_name`, `description`, `label`, `expression`: string literals from macro
- `constraints`: static array slice
- `type_ir`: function pointer

This enables zero-allocation field introspection.

## Why fn() -> TypeIR?

TypeIR construction may involve heap allocation (String fields). Rust doesn't allow this in const contexts. A function pointer defers construction to first use.

